The paper deals with facial landmark estimation using a joint multi-view convolutional network, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of deep learning techniques for this task also suggests a possible fit with machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also evaluates its model on various datasets, which could potentially fall under multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories.
